Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula says the forensic investigation into the Mangaung Bus Rapid Transport System will mainly focus on the alleged price inflation during the procurement of buses. eNCA's Moloko Moloto reports. #DStv403 MANGAUNG - A whopping R103-million has been spent on the Mangaung Bus Rapid Transport System. But five years later, the system hasn't taken off and now there are allegations of corruption and price inflation. Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula says he's instituted a forensic investigation to probe the allegations. * eNCA's Moloko Moloto reports.